# Keep the Docker build context minimal and secret-free.
#
# The git boundary (.gitignore) and the Docker build-context boundary are not
# the same: Docker only honors .dockerignore. Without this file a build run
# after the documented .env is created would pull live CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN /
# CROWDSEC_BOUNCER_KEY values, the local Caddyfile, and persisted ./data into
# the build context even though the Dockerfile never COPYs them.
#
# Allow-list form: exclude everything, then re-include only the paths the
# Dockerfile actually reads from the build context:
#   COPY tests/ ...
#   COPY Caddyfile.example ...
# (All other COPYs use --from=<stage> and never touch the build context.)
*
!Dockerfile
!Caddyfile.example
!tests/
!tests/**
